mediaNotes: Calls and songs (primarily from 2 males but a few calls from the single female present as well) and wings and calls in flight at and after liftoff (twice) and prior to/while landing (once). 2 audio recordings joined together at 2:22 with a 1 second silenced transition. Both audio recordings are of a single female and 2 males (vocalizations here are almost exclusively male though the female was seen calling a few times). First audio begins directly after both males and the female landed atop the eastern most gourd cluster (prior to this the males were vocally pursuing the female aerially), the second audio begins at 2:23 as all 3 fly in to land again on the same gourd complex. Both audio recordings end with all 3 lifting up off gourd complex (the males again beginning their aerial pursuit of the female, singing and calling at her in flight). Nearly all of the audio is of the 2 males singing and calling at the female, initially while perched alongside the female atop the gourd structure, this quickly followed by each male entering a separate gourd and singing and calling from within with head held at gourd entrance while the female remained perched atop structure. The female never entered a gourd.
